verses.roman:
"caitanyera pāriṣada mora mātulera khyāti
'ṭhākurālī' karena gosāñi, tāṅre māre lāthi"

synonyms: caitanyera pāriṣada—associate of Śrī Caitanya Mahāprabhu; mora—my; mātulera—of the maternal uncle; khyāti—reputation; ṭhākurālī—superiority; karena—exhibits; gosāñi—Nityānanda Prabhu; tāṅre—him; māre lāthi—kicks.
translation: "My uncle is well known as one of the associates of Śrī Caitanya Mahāprabhu, but Lord Nityānanda Prabhu asserts His superiority by kicking him."
